text: York is an unincorporated community in Atchison County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== York was founded in 1857 by Archibald York, and named for him. A post office called York was established in 1878, and remained in operation until 1901. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Atchison County, Missouri Category:1857 establishments in Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: York, Missouri
